cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.NA 

This paper deals with complexity classes and computational problems, which are typically studied in the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of potential functions and Lemke paths suggests a connection to sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the reduction of PLCP to EndOfPotentialLine involves numerical methods, which are relevant to sub-category cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
